  "notes": "Northern Kurdish / Kurmanji (kurdî, Kurmancî), the largest Kurdish variety. The mapping above is the 31-letter Hawar Latin alphabet (Celadet Alî Bedirxan, 1932), the script of the ku Wikipedia and of Kurmanji in Turkey, Syria and the diaspora. The Kurdo-Arabic (Sorani-style) alphabet and the former Soviet Cyrillic alphabet are also used for Kurdish and are NOT modelled here — Hawar Latin input is assumed. Aspiration of /p t k/ is contrastive but unwritten.",
